FOR
4 SENATE BILL NO. 710 By: Seifried
5
6
7 An Act relating to teacher preparation; amending
Section 1, Chapter 400, O.S.L. 2025 (70 O.S. Supp.
8 2025, Section 6-186.1), which relates to
establishment of TeachForwardOK; allowing the
9 Commission for Educational Quality and Accountability
to select more than one applicant to receive certain
10 monetary award if funds are sufficient; updating
statutory references; updating statutory language;
11 and declaring an emergency.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 1, Chapter 400, O.S.L.
16 2025 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 6-186.1), is amended to read as
17 follows:
18 Section 6-186.1. A. The Commission for Educational Quality and
19 Accountability shall establish and maintain a two-year pilot program
20 to be known as TeachForwardOK to provide new, high-quality pathways
21 to enter the teaching profession and increase the number of teachers
22 in this state’s workforce.
23 B. Within thirty (30) days of the effective date of this act
24 August 29, 2025, the Commission shall issue a request for proposals
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB710 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 to s elect technical assistance providers to evaluate teacher
2 education programs in institutions of higher education within The
3 Oklahoma State System of Higher Education that are accredited by the
4 Commission pursuant to Section 6-186 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma
5 Statutes this title.
6 C. To participate in TeachForwardOK, a teacher education
7 program shall submit an application to the Commission in the manner
8 and on a form prescribed by the Commission. The Commission shall
9 establish criteria to approve applicants. Subject to the
10 availability of funds, the Commission shall award grants to approved
11 applicant teacher education programs. The Commission may use any
12 gifts, grants, devises, and donations from any public or private
13 source and monies appropriated by the Legislature for the purpose of
14 implementing the provisions of this section. Grants shall be used
15 as incentives to participate and to contract with a technical
16 assistance provider selected by the Commission pursuant to
17 subsection B of this section. The provider shall evaluate, at a
18 minimum, the following:
19 1. Teacher candidate recruitment and completion;
20 2. Whether the teacher education program prepares teacher
21 candidates effectively;
22 3. Whether the teacher education program meets workforce needs
23 in this state; and
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB710 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 4. Innovative ways to recruit nontraditional teacher candidates
2 unique to the teacher education program.
3 D. 1. Evaluation reports prepared by a technical assistance
4 provider shall be electronically submitted to the approved applicant
5 teacher education program and the Commission.
6 2. Within ninety (90) days of receiving the report, the teacher
7 education program shall electronically submit a report response to
8 the Commission detailing how the teacher education program plans to
9 address the evaluation report’s findings. The report response shall
10 prioritize innovative approaches to provide new, high-quality
11 pathways to enter the teaching profession and increase the number of
12 teachers in this state’s workforce including, but not limited to:
13 a. developing a system for recruiting eligible teacher
14 candidates, such as:
15 (1) a pathway for high school students to become
16 paraprofessionals,
17 (2) a pathway for paraprofessionals to become
18 teachers, and
19 (3) a pathway for individuals with bachelor’s degrees
20 to become teachers,
21 b. developing a curriculum that includes intensive on-
22 the-job training for teacher candidates,
23 c. identifying a mastery-based evaluation system to
24 determine when eligible teacher candidates have
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB710 SFLR Page 3
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 mastered the skills and competencies necessary for
2 graduation from an apprenticeship program and
3 outlining benchmarks that teacher candidates must meet
4 as they progress through on-the-job training,
5 d. offering a schedule that enables teacher candidates to
6 work full time full-time in a public school district
7 while participating in an apprenticeship program and
8 allowing paraprofessionals to continue in their
9 positions, or
10 e. providing a flexible schedule for paraprofessionals
11 participating in an apprenticeship program to support
12 their success in the program that will facilitate
13 course completion and on-the-job training.
14 E. Subject to the availability of funding, the Commission shall
15 review the report responses submitted pursuant to subsection D of
16 this section and select one approved applicant teacher education
17 program to receive Five Hundred Thousand Dollars ($500,000.00) to
18 enact the initiatives outlined in the program’s report response. If
19 funds are sufficient, the Commission may select more than one
20 approved applicant teacher education program to receive a monetary
21 award based on the report response submitted pursuant to subsection
22 D of this section to enact the initiatives outlined in the report
23 response.
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB710 SFLR Page 4
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 F. By December 31, 2027, the Commission shall electronically
2 submit a report of TeachForwardOK’s findings and recommendations to
3 the Governor, the President Pro Tempore of the Senate, and the
4 Speaker of the House of Representatives.
5 G. The Commission shall promulgate rules to implement the
6 provisions of this section.
7 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
8 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
9 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
10 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
